Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
fixAllIos(25.10)                                              fixAllIos(25.10)

Name
       fixAllIos - Changes the status of all I/O pins, I/O cells, or CLASS PAD
       AREAIO cells to a FIXED state to keep them from being reassigned

Syntax
        fixAllIos

       [-help]

       [-pinOnly | -cellOnly | -incAreaIo]

       Changes  the  status  of  all  I/O pins, I/O cells, or CLASS PAD AREAIO
       cells to a FIXED state to keep them from  being  reassigned.  Use  this
       command after importing the design.

Parameters
       -cellOnly
              Changes the status of all I/O cells to a FIXED state.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each fixAllIos parameter.  For  a  detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command:

              man fixAllIos

       -incAreaIo
              Changes the status of all CLASS PAD  AREAIO  cells  to  a  FIXED
              state.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -pinOnly
              Changes the status of all I/O pins to a FIXED state.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Examples
              * The  following  command changes the status of all I/O pins and
                I/O cells to a FIXED state:

                fixAllIos

                Note: This is the default functionality.

              * The following command changes the status of all I/O pins to  a
                FIXED state:

                fixAllIos -pinOnly

              * The following command changes the status of all I/O cells to a
                FIXED state:

                fixAllIos -cellOnly

              * The  following command changes the status of all I/O pins, I/O
                cells, and all CLASS PAD AREAIO cells to a FIXED state:

                fixAllIos -incAreaIo

Related Information
              * unfixAllIos

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide.

